revision.text:
{{Infobox Protected area | name = Ajidaar-Unkyur | iucn_category = III | photo = | photo_caption = | location = [[Nookat District]], [[Osh Region]], [[Kyrgyzstan]] | nearest_city = | coordinates = | area = | established = 1975 | visitation_num = | visitation_year = | governing_body = }} '''Ajidaar-Unkyur''' is a geological protected area (karst cave) located at slopes of Teo-Muyun Mountains in [[Osh Region]] of [[Kyrgyzstan]]. Its total length is about 100 m. The cave is inhabited by a large bat colony ([[Lesser Mouse-Eared Bat]] and [[Greater Horseshoe Bat]]).<ref name="encyc">{{cite book|title=Ошская область: Энциклопедия|trans-title=Osh Oblast Encyclopedia |first=|last=|publisher=Chief Editorial Board of Kyrgyz Soviet Encyclopedia|language= Russian|location=Frunze|year=1994|isbn=|pages=445}}</ref>
