[[Category:Flora of Canada|*]] [[Category:Lists of plants]]

This is a '''list of [[mountain pass]]es and hills in the [[Tour de France]]'''. Among the passes most often crossed, [[Col du Tourmalet]], [[Col d'Aubisque]], [[Col d'Aspin]], [[Col de Peyresourde]], [[Col du Galibier]] and [[Col de la Faucille]] dominate, while the highest peak ever reached is [[Cime de la Bonette-Restefond]] ({{convert|2802|m|abbr=on}}), used in the [[1962 Tour de France|1962]], [[1964 Tour de France|1964]], [[1993 Tour de France|1993]] and [[2008 Tour de France]].<ref name=guide>{{cite book|last=Augendre|first=Jacques|title=Le Tour de France - Guide Historique|year=2010|pages=190–214|url=http://www.letour.com/2009/TDF/COURSE/docs/TDF10_Historique_VERSION%20INTEGRALE.pdf|accessdate=22 May 2011|language=French}}</ref>
The highest mountain finishes in the history of the Tour were Galibier (2,645 m (8,677&nbsp;ft)) in 2011; previously this had been [[Val Thorens]] ({{convert|2275|m|abbr=on}}) in [[1994 Tour de France|1994]]; and before that [[Col du Granon]] ({{convert|2413|m|abbr=on}}) used in [[1986 Tour de France|1986]].<ref name=guide />
{{TOC limit|2}}
