==2007 Tour de France== The [[2007 Tour de France]] included 22 mountain passes or summit finishes, categorized HC, 1, or 2.
In 2007, the Tour had a stage finish at the summit of [[Col d'Aubisque]] ({{convert|1709|m|abbr=on}}) for the first time. Earlier that year the riders crossed the [[Alps]], both [[Col de l'Iseran]] ({{convert|2770|m|abbr=on}}) and [[Col du Galibier]] ({{convert|2645|m|abbr=on}}) on the same stage.<ref name=guide />
